  "texts": [
    "This method builds on the Euclidean pSp method (Richardson et al., 2021) for image-to-image translation.",
    "The pSp method uses a feature pyramid to extract feature maps and uses a set of projection heads on these feature maps to produce each of the style vectors required by StyleGAN (Karras et al., 2019 (Karras et al.,, 2020)), which is commonly denoted the W + -space.",
    "Imageto-image translation can then be done by editing or replacing style vectors.",
